# Suggested Finds — Investment Intent

This rule captures the fundamental purpose of each discovery archetype.
**Never ask keerti to re-explain this. It is settled.**

## Steady Compounders — Long-Term Accumulation (Years)

- **Holding horizon:** Multi-year. Buy and hold through market cycles.
- **Alpha source:** Business quality + reinvestment rate. NOT news or catalysts.
- **Industries:** Boring, AI-proof — logistics, waste, utilities, insurance, distribution, HVAC, pest control, food distribution, specialty chemicals, water treatment.
- **Quality bar:** ROE > 12%, positive FCF, low beta (<1.3), durable margins.
- **Auto-trade rules:** Full conviction sizing (up to 1.5x), all 3 dip-buy tiers enabled, no sleeve cap.
- **Sell when:** P/E >> growth rate (valuation stretched) OR fundamentals deteriorate (ROE drops, FCF goes negative, leverage spikes).

## Gold Mines — Near-Term Catalyst Plays (6–12 Months)

- **Holding horizon:** 6–12 months. NOT a 2–3 year plan. Theme plays out → exit.
- **Alpha source:** Macro theme catalyst that is active RIGHT NOW in headlines.
- **Sectors:** Growth/catalyst-oriented — AI & Semiconductors, Healthcare & Biotech, Defense & Aerospace, Clean Energy, Cybersecurity, Consumer Brands, Financials, Tech & Software.
- **Quality bar:** Still must be fundamentally sound (profitable or near-profitable, growing revenue, real moat). Not speculative.
- **Auto-trade rules:** Conviction capped at 1.25x, Gold Mine sleeve capped at 40% of long-term allocation, Tier 3 dip-buy disabled, blocked when SPY < SMA200.
- **Sell when:** Macro catalyst fades or reverses, stock hits price target, or company stops benefiting from the theme.

## Key Distinctions

| | Steady Compounder | Gold Mine |
|---|---|---|
| Horizon | Years | 6–12 months |
| Thesis | Business quality | Macro catalyst |
| Dip tiers | All 3 | Tier 1 + 2 only |
| SPY block | No | Yes (SPY < SMA200) |
| Sleeve cap | None | 40% of LT allocation |
| Exit trigger | Valuation/fundamentals | Theme inflection |

